snippet.textDisplay: There are several issues going on at same time which makes us not good enough right now but the number 1 problem we have is because when we beat celtic it was such a high, a rush of euphoria its almost like a drug that we're on a come down from.  Particularly with the winter break coming right afterwards definitely didn't help as had there been a midweek game or even a game the following week there would have been a chance to still ride the high & keep the momentum going or even if we'd lost there would have been an anger so there would have been a chance to take it out on whoever was up next and blow them away but because there was a 3 week break there was a come down and its hard to get all psyched up to the same place they were on 30th December the day after the game.  However even although this is the main reason for the sudden change in the performances, they really should be able to mentally get over that and be up for the challange to get these results we need and ride through the wee dip to build up to the pre old firm game form and it's the mark of champs to be able to do that.  Celtic lost to us but picked themselves up again and won all their games since.  They simply should be good enough to win against the bottom of the league side and beat Aberdeen at Ibrox! They played like they're a mid table side post split and can't be relegated but also can't get into top 6 so it's just a nothing to play for match, definitely not like title contenders!  Stevie G get yer finger out and put hagi on at half time rather than 76mins or at least on at 60 mins instead of oslow!

snippet.textDisplay:
I am sitting here shaking my head at some of the comments on this thread.
Some people have forgotten the state of the club when the manager took over and the progress that has been made since.
Phase One I think is over. He laid down a marker on what it means to play for the shirt and got the team organized and hard to beat.
It's fairly obvious there is too much reliance on one guy to get the goals and Phase Two will be on developing the ability to break down well-organized defences and getting more goals from the rest of the team, especially the CAMs and wingers.
Before he came, there was not a cat in hell's chance of signing a top rated young star like Ianis Hagi.
It's a journey. Rome was not built in a day.
I get it that some are disappointed in the stop-gap striker, but am confident that had a better one been available, they would not have hesitated to sign him. In any event, once young Ianis finds his feet, we will all be in for a treat.

snippet.textDisplay: I'm not a manager or a coach... but for me its not hard to work out why 2 number 10's work against the likes of celtic,feyenoord,porto and not against hearts, aberdeen, and ross county... 11 men behind the ball means there is no space for either number 10 to be creative or space to create, the reason it works well in europe or celtic is because they dont have 11 men behind the ball, but the confusing part for me is steven knows this as he says in this interview but decides to switch formation in the last 5 minutes, he always sticks with his trusted 2 number 10's in a free role formation but when it comes to the league when teams are putting 11 men behind the ball and our number 10's have no space to create then for me he has to look at starting the game with a different approach in terms of tactics rather than 5 minutes before the end.... 11 men behind the ball at ibrox and mcgregor getting man of the match kind of explains it all.

snippet.textDisplay: Garbage performance. If we're not creating chances, why wait until the 76th minute before bringing on Hagi, then the 83rd minute before bringing on Kamberi? I've defended Ojo all season, but is he the man to turn a high-pressure game into a win (has it ever been done before?)? How many times do we have to watch Ryan Kent (who I love) cut inside onto his right foot before ballooning the ball across the Atlantic? I read a quote saying we still have two Old Firm games to go...yes, but they'll be two meaningless games at this rate.
